See above. I wasn't able to hold onto the words long enough to repeat many of them.
I think it would have been easier if I'd been able to look at the objects for as long as I wanted. But you knew that.

The recall itself was difficult, not the way the task was presented. I appreciated that the words fit in categories; that gave me something to grasp onto, but overall I found it tough to repeat randomish lists of words.
I've done some memory surveys before, and they always make me worry. Thanks for including a variety of tasks so I could feel good about some of them.
THE MAIN SPEAKER WAS TALKING TO HIS SON AS PART OF THE STORYCORPS PROJECT.
WHEN HE WAS A BOY, HIS FAMILY WAS VERY POOR, THOUGH HE AT FIRST THOUGHT THEY WERE RICH.
HIS FATHER GOT A JOB WORKING AS CUSTODIAN AT THE PUBLIC LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER DID A GREAT JOB AS CUSTODIAN, SO GOOD THAT YOU COULD SEE THE TOPS OF BOOKSHELVES GLEAMING.
THE FAMILY LIVED IN THE LIBRARY BUILDING.
THE BOY WAS AT FIRST EMBARRASSED BECAUSE HIS LIVING ARRANGEMENTS WERE DIFFERENT FROM THE OTHER KIDS'.
BUT LIVING IN THE LIBRARY HAD GREAT PERKS.
BEST OF THE PERKS WAS THE UNFETTERED ACCESS TO BOOKS, SO MANY BOOKS.
THE BOY WOULD LOOK UP ANSWERS TO ANY QUESTIONS HE HAD; STAY UP TILL 3 A.
HE GREW UP WITH A LOVE OF KNOWLEDGE.
HE WAS THE FIRST IN THE FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE, AND HE EVENTUALLY BECAME A UNIVERSITY PROFESSOR.
HE SHOWED HIS FATHER HIS COLLEGE OFFICE WITH HIS NAME ON THE DOOR, AND THOUGH HIS DAD DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING HE COULD TELL HE WAS PROUD.
HE DOESN'T KNOW WHERE HE'D BE IF IT WEREN'T FOR GROWING UP IN THE LIBRARY.
RONALD GREW UP POOR, THOUGH HE AT FIRST THOUGHT HE WAS RICH.
HIS PARENTS TOLD HIM THEY WERE POOR.
HIS DAD GOT A JOB AS A JANITOR, A CUSTODIAN, AT THE PUBLIC LIBRARY.
THE FAMILY LIVED AT THE LIBRARY, WHICH AT FIRST EMBARRASSED RONALD.
BUT HE LEARNED THAT LIVING IN THE LIBRARY WAS COOL.
BEST OF ALL, HE HAD ACCESS TO ALL THE BOOKS, AND COULD READ AS MUCH AS HE LIKED.
ANYTIME HE HAD A QUESTION ABOUT ANYTHING HE COULD LOOK UP THE ANSWER.
HE WOULD READ UNTIL 3 IN THE MORNING.
HIS LOVE OF LEARNING TOOK HIM TO COLLEGE, AND HE EVENTUALLY GOT A JOB AS A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.
HE SHOWED HIS DAD HIS OFFICE AT COLLEGE.
HIS DAD WAS QUIET BUT RONALD COULD TELL HE WAS PROUD.
THE STORY WAS TOLD BY RONALD TO HIS SON AS PART OF STORYCORPS.
OH, AND DAD WAS SUCH A GOOD CUSTODIAN THAT HE EVEN WAXED THE TOPS OF BOOKSHELVES SO YOU COULD SEE THEM GLEAM.
RONALD HAD TO BE QUIET IN THE LIBRARY DURING THE DAY, BUT AFTER HOURS HE COULD RUN AND PLAY.
HE WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE.
